{
  "text": "The Hap protein of H. in£uenzae was reported to release its functional domain into the medium by autoproteolytic cleavage [CITATION_1] . Such release was not observed for the Hia protein [CITATION_2] . To investigate whether the neisserial homologs are proteolytically cleaved in E. coli, medium of E. coli cells expressing the proteins was concentrated by TCA precipitation and analyzed by SDS^PAGE. In neither case was a secreted product detected in the medium.",
